Heyo guys! Finally got some time to chop a segment up from this dope interview and share it with ya! A few weeks ago I was a guest on @hella__chluy podcast @chluytalkpodcast 🎙, a fellow Cambodian American 🇰🇭🇺🇸 Someone who I have watched and admired over the years, with his comedy skits and music parodies 😅. I swear everyone can relate to your jokes 😂🙏 Anyways, here’s a segment where I actually opened up a lot about what’s been behind the scenes during the pandemic, how we stayed through it and other cool things we talked about that I haven’t mentioned really before. 

Full podcast is about an HOUR long and you can find it on his bio // ITunes and on his youtube. So sit back, tune in and let me know your thoughts! 

Thanks again @hella__chluy for having me! I’ll be sharing more segments here and there as well 🙏

Time flies when your having fun!💯

The past couple of months at the @live_fit_apparel HQ have been a crazy but fun journey!! Almost a year ago when the pandemic started I felt as if I was drowning, really spreading myself thin when we had to furlough most of our staff. It was fucking MENTAL 🤯 but damn did I have to dig deep and start what felt like, from scratch📝 Training, developing, re-structuring and working on my own leadership skills. And damn was it worth it… these are just a FRACTION of what’s been going on behind closed doors with the new squad 🙏 Thankful for my team💯 We’re going full speed !! 

#LVFT #livefit #livefitapparel #TEAMLVFT 

Music: @shaker - Somebody.

Thank you guys for tuning in, I’ve been MIA with the entrepreneurial side of things solely because I actually have businesses to run 😂🤷🏽‍♂️. But I’ve been asked constantly about how I’m dealing with the statewide “stay at home” issue and what people should be doing. First of all, I’m no expert on these things, I’m just sharing my personal views and opinions as a CEO, designer and business owner.

A lot of these things, companies should already be doing, but now since we are all at home with plenty of down time, we should look a little deeper into each subject.

Here are a few tips I shared within this video for pretty much everyone that has a brand, a personal brand, a company and or business; doesn’t matter if it’s an e-commerce based business or a service business: - PERSONAL LEVEL COMMUNICATION WITH YOUR CUSTOMERS. *Constructive criticism. - PATCH BLEEDING HOLES *Analyze and regroup.
- RE-BRANDING *Website Facelift. *New Marketing Campaign Ideas. *New color schemes. *Possible new logos and categories. -DO NOT PAY ATTENTION TO YOUR COMPETITION. *Focus on what you’re good at and know 😉. Thanks again for watching. Drop a comment, share this and start hammering these out!! 😬🔥💻📊📈

This Saturday the official LIVE FIT. Bootcamp will be held here at the LVFT. HQ Hosted by myself @randall_pich and head trainer @thomasj_usa . Link is in bio for more details and admission. 
Why a bootcamp? Well live fit apparel would of never existed if it wasn’t for my prior career in personal training. With that being said, LVFT always had deep roots in the field of exercise and kinesiology. With 8 years of extensive experience training clients of all ages, running bootcamps and small group training I decided to get back to his roots and open the doors back up and focus on building with the local community again. This time around I’ll have Thomas alongside, a pro MMA fighter and experienced personal trainer, training and running the bootcamp as well. 
So if you haven’t, head to the link, grab a ticket and come prepared Saturday morning! And yes, you know the whole group will get a ton of LVFT goodies and afterwards we’ll enjoy some desserts provided by @paderiabakehouse 🤘🏽😁. Let’s go!

Heyo guys! Finally got some time to chop a segment up from this dope interview and share it with ya! Full podcast is about an HOUR long and you can find it on his bio // ITunes and on his youtube. So sit back, tune in and let me know your thoughts! 

Thanks again @hella__chluy for having me! I’ll be sharing more segments here and there as well 🙏

Time flies when your having fun!💯

The past couple of months at the @live_fit_apparel HQ have been a crazy but fun journey!! Almost a year ago when the pandemic started I felt as if I was drowning, really spreading myself thin when we had to furlough most of our staff. It was fucking MENTAL 🤯 but damn did I have to dig deep and start what felt like, from scratch📝 Training, developing, re-structuring and working on my own leadership skills. And damn was it worth it… these are just a FRACTION of what’s been going on behind closed doors with the new squad 🙏 Thankful for my team💯 We’re going full speed !!
